    <title>Class equation: abelian groups</title>
    <statement>
    <p>
    Prove: a finite group <m>\abs{G}</m> is abelian if and only if its class equation is of the form 
    <me>
        \abs{G}=1+1+\cdots +1
    </me>.
    </p>
    </statement>
